heaviest_rainfall.status: The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm fell at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour over the 37.2 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today ranked 5th for the heaviest rainfall ever in our records, with a peak intensity of 11.8mm per hour sustained for 2.1 hours, resulting in a total accumulation of 7.28mm.  27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: On 04 January 2025, the rain lasted for 37.2 hours, which is the longest time recorded by our database.  36.8mm accumulated and it fell at 4.6mm per hour at times.

summary.description:
Today, a bit warmer for the feels like temperature (up 3.2°C) and outside temperature (up 2.3°C), more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 13%), and drier conditions in rainfall (down 0.3 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in rainfall (up 0.3 mm) and cloud levels (up 1058 m).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1171 m), feels like temperature (up 2.6°C), outside temperature (up 1.8°C), and inside temperature (up 1.8°C) when compared to today.
